  "prompt": "Should I confess to my crush of 6 years ?",
  "response": "Confessing your feelings to your crush of 6 years is a big step, and it\u2019s natural to feel nervous about it! Here are some things to consider to help you decide:\n\n### 1. **How well do you know them?**\n   - Have you built a friendship or connection over these years? If they know you well, they may already have a sense of your feelings or be more open to hearing them.\n   - If you\u2019re not close, consider whether confessing might come out of nowhere and catch them off guard.\n\n### 2. **What are the potential outcomes?**\n   - **Positive outcome:** They might feel the same way, and your relationship could deepen.\n   - **Neutral outcome:** They might not feel the same but appreciate your honesty and value your friendship.\n   - **Negative outcome:** They might feel awkward or distant afterward. Consider whether you\u2019re prepared for this possibility.\n\n### 3. **Why now?**\n   - What\u2019s motivating you to confess after 6 years? Is it because you feel ready to take the risk, or is there pressure from external factors? Make sure it\u2019s something you truly want to do.\n\n### 4. **How will it impact you?**\n   - Even if they don\u2019t feel the same, expressing your feelings can be liberating and help you move forward. Holding onto unspoken feelings for so long can be emotionally draining.\n\n### 5. **How should you approach it?**\n   - Be honest but respectful. Avoid putting too much pressure on them or making it overly dramatic.\n   - Choose a private and comfortable setting to have the conversation.\n\n### Final Thoughts:\nIf you\u2019ve been holding onto these feelings for 6 years, it might be worth sharing them for your own peace of mind. Just be prepared for any outcome and remember that their response doesn\u2019t define your worth. Whether you confess or not, you\u2019ve already shown a lot of courage by considering this step.\n\nGood luck\u2014you\u2019ve got this! \ud83d\udcaa\ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
